The paper deals with the operational semantics of a lambda calculus for probabilistic programming, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the adaptation of the classic operational semantics of lambda calculus to a continuous setting, which involves mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also deals with inference techniques, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation technique of trace Markov chain Monte Carlo, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
